radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 8 mm with hyperemia and adjacent fascial thickening. There is a moderate amount of intermediate density free fluid in the pelvis. There is no free air or organized fluid collection. The lung bases are clear. The visualized portions of the heart and pericardium are normal. The liver enhances homogenously and there is no focal liver lesion. The portal veins are patent. The gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, and adrenals are normal. The kidneys enhance symmetrically and excrete contrast without evidence of hydronephrosis or mass. There is no bowel obstruction. There is no lytic or blastic lesion worrisome for malignancy.
